    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and it's not just that it's \"fascinating,\" it's almost like they're careful about it. my manager won't even look at these specific batches, and they always redirect me to the basic stuff if I ask questions about the trends. it's like they know i'm seeing something, but they need me to just keep my head down and keep typing. do you think it's possible the higher-ups are intentionally keeping the actual scale of this from the people actually doing the work?",
