      "content": "\"defensive mechanism\"... that's exactly it. It feels like I'm holding the blueprints to the whole thing and they're treating me like I'm just cleaning floors. it's actually kind of scary when you think about it—if i'm seeing these massive shifts in the transaction flows, and they're actively hiding the \"why\" from everyone else, then i'm basically the only one who knows how the new system is actually being constructed. how can a company have an entire global restructuring happening right under everyone's noses without anyone noticing?",
